raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: laspy
  version: 2.7.0

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f56feb5445e75d6ff12ee814aab6a35339290e75264ff277c6bf553f3025a3f5

build:
  number: 1
  skip: python_impl == 'pypy'
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then: python
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then: cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then: numpy
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - numpy
    - lazrs-python
    - setuptools
    - m2r2
    - hatch
  run:
    - python
    - numpy
    - lazrs-python
    - m2r2

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - laspy
  - files:
      source:
        - tests/*
    requirements:
      run:
        - pytest
    script:
      - pytest -v

about:
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Native Python ASPRS LAS read/write library
  description: |
    Laspy is a python library for reading, modifying and creating LAS LiDAR files.
  homepage: https://github.com/laspy/laspy
  repository: https://github.com/laspy/laspy
  documentation: https://laspy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - plimkilde
    - hobu
    - chambbj
